      <div class="msgContentFrame">AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAARRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRGH! <br /> <br />I am just about fed up and ready to rip my computer apart so I can't play until this POS crafting system gets fixed so you feel like you're beating your head against a damn wall just to make something to level! Even when that item is 5 levels or more below you! <br /> <br />UGH! What is pissing me off right now is the crafting skills though. <br /> <br />SE, If I level a job to 10, spend the 3 points to equip the skill, and I am allowed to use said skill once per synth, then that skill better pop up before I even choose the first action and STAY UP UNTIL I !#%&quot;#$&amp;#!$&quot;# USE IT! No more of this pop up fine then not pop up at all for 5+ ENTIRE SYNTHS at a time! <br /> <br /> <br />On another note, I think you guys are really setting yourselves up to shoot yourselves in the foot. One major patch a month may be fine for maintaining a game, but with the game in it's current state and your desire to rebuild faith... you'd be much better off doing SMALL patches weekly along with a major patch. Small things like updating the stack size should be easy to put in on a weekly basis and they will at least make some parts of the game less frustrating for people... making people wait... makes people build up expectations... and when those expectations are not met... don't expect them to pay to wait around another month for another potential disappointment... <br /> <br />I really want to like the game. I am trying... but everywhere I go, I run into something that frustrates me...<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>行く河の流れは絶えずしてしかも元の水にあらず。よどみに浮かぶ泡沫はかつ消えかつ結びて久しくとどまりたる例なし世の中にある人と住みかも全くのごとき。　－方丈記</div></div>
